  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nI seem to be having trouble signing transactions when the network id is 4447. Specifically, I'm using this library: https://github.com/se3000/ruby-eth. I'm not sure if the problem is with ruby-eth or what, but when I hack things and change the network_id to something small (e.g. anything between 1-100) everything works just fine. Just wondering why 4447 was chosen specifically.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version: 4.0.1\r\n",
